text.tspan: On startup, a 3 columns layout is shown.
The 1st column gives an overview of all the tags and
saved searches, which can be used to apply
The second column shows all the papers, sorted
by date. The list is reduced when a filter is
applied, or when the search bar is used.
The third column shows the selected paper
(on startup, the most recent). On smaller screens,
only a fraction of the width of the page may be visible.
Reducing to a 2 columns layout should keep
the software perfectly usable with small screens.
keep focus on content. It is best used with the
A button, always located at the top left of the window,
reveals a popover to switch between layouts.
A blue disc appears in the export button
to notify there is a queue pending.
The queue allows to export a bunch of papers,
as well as pages picked up from here and there, all at once.
The expand buttons shows the pages to be exported
Clicking the page number selects it in the reader,
If the user realizes she is actually not interested with this page,
she can remove it from the queue.
It is possible to send documents to a queue,
from a dropdown menu in the document list.
Single pages can be sent to the queue the same way papers are,
using overlaid controls (visible after scan and while scrolling).
The "export" button reveals a popover allowing
to export the current document by different manners.
